-- Newcastle Manager Pardew Accused of Misconduct in Tottenham Game
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2012-08-20T17:32:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-20/newcastle-manager-pardew-accused-of-misconduct-in-tottenham-game.html
Newcastle United soccer manager  Alan
Pardew  was accused of misconduct by the Football Association for
pushing an assistant referee during the 2-1 win over Tottenham
two days ago.  Pardew publicly apologized for the incident after the
Premier League game. He has until 4 p.m. on Aug. 23 to make a
formal response to the F.A.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Peter-Joseph Hegarty at 
 phegarty@bloomberg.net  